-- Hong Kong shares fall to 10-week low, down 3 pct on the week
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Fri Jan 24, 2014 03:09AM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 24 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares fell to their lowest close since Nov. 13 on Friday as worries about Chinese growth lingered the day after a disappointing manufacturing survey came out.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 1.3 percent on the day to 22,2450.1,  and lost 3.0 percent for the week.  This was its biggest weekly drop since June. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong slid 0.9 percent for the day and fell 1.5 on the week.